<exercise id="fs-id1171890389510" print-placement="end"><problem id="fs-id1171886418543">
    <para id="id2259390">In <link document="m24171" target-id="fs-id4889487">Exercise 11</link> from "Problems on Minterm Analysis," we have the following data:
A survey of a represenative group of students yields the following information:
    <list id="eip-id1166817946721"><item>52 percent are male</item>
    <item>85 percent live on campus</item>
    <item>78 percent are male or are active in intramural sports (or both)</item>
    <item>30 percent live on campus but are not active in sports</item>
    <item>32 percent are male, live on campus, and are active in sports</item>
    <item>8  percent are male and live off campus</item>
    <item>17 percent are male students inactive in sports</item></list></para>
