</item>
      <item id="uid8243524234524352">Suppose a person has a university education (no graduate study). What is
the (conditional) probability that he or she will make $25,000 or more?
</item>
      <item id="uid923452345345">Find the total probability that a person's income category is at least
as high as his or her educational level.

</item>
    </list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id5370446">
 
    <!--empty paragraphs get left behind.-->
    <list id="id68992" display="block" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item id="uid4">
        
        <m:math overflow="scroll">
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mi>P</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo>(</m:mo>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>E</m:mi>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>S</m:mi>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo>)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
